00:17:27,077 --> 00:17:30,779
And the screen dims, it goes into the scope view,

410
00:17:30,819 --> 00:17:33,440
it feels very Halo, it looks almost like a sniper scope.

411
00:17:34,041 --> 00:17:36,182
And it works really great on the controller.

412
00:17:37,003 --> 00:17:38,764
So before we shipped Halo Wars 2,

413
00:17:38,884 --> 00:17:41,645
we actually created Halo Wars Definitive Edition,

414
00:17:42,166 --> 00:17:45,007
ported it to PC, and tried to bring over these powers

415
00:17:45,027 --> 00:17:48,129
in a way that felt good for PC and mouse controls.

416
00:17:49,050 --> 00:17:52,934
And it turned out these ended up being a lot harder to implement on the PC than we expected.

417
00:17:53,915 --> 00:17:55,636
You can kind of think about it in some different ways.

418
00:17:55,716 --> 00:18:00,661
So for example, without the cursor here, your normal PC cursor, you get a little bit lost

419
00:18:00,721 --> 00:18:01,822
in terms of what you're targeting.

420
00:18:02,343 --> 00:18:06,467
It also never quite felt responsive enough even if we mapped it to the mouse in a way

421
00:18:06,487 --> 00:18:07,488
that we thought made sense.

422
00:18:08,208 --> 00:18:10,289
If we tried to leave the main PC cursor up,

423
00:18:10,309 --> 00:18:12,390
then you'd have this double cursor thing going on.

424
00:18:12,830 --> 00:18:14,351
And if we kind of got rid of the overlay,

425
00:18:14,371 --> 00:18:16,312
then it just didn't really have that same level

426
00:18:16,352 --> 00:18:18,753
of anticipation and excitement of deploying these powers.

427
00:18:20,353 --> 00:18:21,354
So ultimately, for Halo Wars 2.

428
00:18:22,630 --> 00:18:25,391
We moved to a model where the reticles are more friendly

