00:19:43,067 --> 00:19:45,288
and apply it in new ways for new modes

462
00:19:45,348 --> 00:19:46,308
and new ways to play the game.

463
00:19:48,791 --> 00:19:50,472
As I mentioned, you know, again, with our assumptions

464
00:19:50,512 --> 00:19:52,412
around the Blitz mode, it's really rethinking

465
00:19:52,452 --> 00:19:53,253
our frame of reference.

466
00:19:53,553 --> 00:19:56,874
So sometimes we might have a tendency as designers

467
00:19:56,974 --> 00:19:59,015
to kind of spin on something for a long time

468
00:19:59,535 --> 00:20:00,915
because we feel like there's a better solution

469
00:20:00,935 --> 00:20:01,556
that's available.

470
00:20:02,656 --> 00:20:05,037
And for us, this was a key piece of, again,

471
00:20:05,077 --> 00:20:06,658
thinking about the deck sizes for Blitz,

472
00:20:06,718 --> 00:20:08,538
where really just thinking about the deck size

473
00:20:08,558 --> 00:20:10,259
in a different way and depth in a different way

474
00:20:10,299 --> 00:20:12,340
and how we make those choices,

475
00:20:12,800 --> 00:20:14,480
it simplified a lot of our design around

476
00:20:14,561 --> 00:20:17,362
how we build out the UI for those pieces of that game.

477
00:20:19,507 --> 00:20:21,127
And finally, embrace trade-offs.

478
00:20:21,447 --> 00:20:23,908
So as I mentioned, we had to move from being a console

479
00:20:23,928 --> 00:20:25,969
title to a multi-platform cross-play title.

480
00:20:26,869 --> 00:20:31,591
And while it's true that we did lose some elements of what

